  "label": "Docketmarked Bedchamber",
  "description": "This narrow bedchamber occupies an upper-floor cell of Ashlar Registry House, its walls built of salvaged ashlar patched with newer brick and limewash. A low cot and a plain chest stand beneath a shuttered slit-window backed by iron grillework, keeping light sparse and drafts controlled. Docket marks and tally scratches score the deep lintel and doorframe, reflecting the dwelling’s administrative purpose even in its private spaces. A small lockbox niche set into the masonry reinforces the house’s routine of sealed papers, hazard notices, and licensed custody.",
